            If Ofgem had been around in the immediate post-war period, two things would be certain: first, the hydro stations would never have been built and secondly, there would have been no benefit in their being built in the north of Scotland. Neither would have been allowed by Ofgem.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0424P1_20040908_WH_42'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-mike-weir' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0424P1_20040908_WH_42' title='Link to this speech by Mr Mike Weir' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
